00:32:19.310 --> 00:32:22.860 align:middle line:10%
of what's been happening.

00:32:22.860 --> 00:32:25.310 align:middle line:84%
I always talk about
myself, it turns out.

00:32:25.310 --> 00:32:29.240 align:middle line:84%
But those of you that know,
know that it isn't really me,

00:32:29.240 --> 00:32:30.890 align:middle line:90%
it's us.

00:32:30.890 --> 00:32:32.990 align:middle line:84%
And I just use myself
as a case study,

00:32:32.990 --> 00:32:36.950 align:middle line:84%
that I know better than I know
everybody else's case study.

00:32:36.950 --> 00:32:43.050 align:middle line:84%
Because what awes me is how
parallel our journeys are,

00:32:43.050 --> 00:32:46.080 align:middle line:84%
and how much-- when I'm going
through something and I think,

00:32:46.080 --> 00:32:49.292 align:middle line:84%
boy, this is really
leading edge stuff--

00:32:49.292 --> 00:32:51.747 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:32:51.747 --> 00:32:52.730 align:middle line:90%


00:32:52.730 --> 00:32:55.403 align:middle line:84%
--I meet somebody
and they say, gee,

00:32:55.403 --> 00:32:57.070 align:middle line:84%
that's just what's
been happening to me.

00:32:57.070 --> 00:33:01.390 align:middle line:90%


00:33:01.390 --> 00:33:03.100 align:middle line:90%
>> No, let's set up in here.

00:33:03.100 --> 00:33:05.222 align:middle line:90%
Let's all sit together.

00:33:05.222 --> 00:33:06.680 align:middle line:84%
>> Now, in the
course of the years,

00:33:06.680 --> 00:33:09.730 align:middle line:84%
I've developed a lot of
very strange friends.

00:33:09.730 --> 00:33:13.390 align:middle line:84%
And one of them is a
being named Emmanuel.

00:33:13.390 --> 00:33:15.670 align:middle line:84%
And Emmanuel is interesting,
because Emmanuel

00:33:15.670 --> 00:33:18.310 align:middle line:90%
doesn't have a body.

00:33:18.310 --> 00:33:21.820 align:middle line:90%
He's a being on another plane.

00:33:21.820 --> 00:33:25.000 align:middle line:84%
And I know some of you here
have a difficult time accepting

00:33:25.000 --> 00:33:27.520 align:middle line:90%
my friend Emmanuel.

00:33:27.520 --> 00:33:30.370 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you'd accept any of my
other friends, but somehow--

00:33:30.370 --> 00:33:36.393 align:middle line:84%
you say you have no prejudices
about color, sex, religion,

00:33:36.393 --> 00:33:38.560 align:middle line:84%
but bodies, somehow if
somebody doesn't have a body,

00:33:38.560 --> 00:33:42.130 align:middle line:84%
you immediately don't know
that you want to accept them.

00:33:42.130 --> 00:33:44.440 align:middle line:84%
But I feel that's your problem,
because he's my friend.

00:33:44.440 --> 00:33:48.400 align:middle line:84%
And either way, I figured is
I'll take my teachings anywhere

00:33:48.400 --> 00:33:50.020 align:middle line:90%
I can get them, OK?

00:33:50.020 --> 00:33:52.630 align:middle line:84%
I don't care whether you got
a body or which kind it is.

00:33:52.630 --> 00:33:55.180 align:middle line:84%
If you got a
teaching, I want it.

00:33:55.180 --> 00:33:57.400 align:middle line:84%
And Emmanuel said to me
when I said to Emmanuel,

00:33:57.400 --> 00:34:00.160 align:middle line:90%
what work do I have to do now?

00:34:00.160 --> 00:34:01.780 align:middle line:84%
He said, Ram Dass,
you're in a school.

00:34:01.780 --> 00:34:03.774 align:middle line:84%
Why don't you try
taking the curriculum?

00:34:03.774 --> 00:34:06.094 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:34:06.094 --> 00:34:07.486 align:middle line:90%


00:34:07.486 --> 00:34:09.210 align:middle line:90%
He said, you took a human birth.

00:34:09.210 --> 00:34:10.470 align:middle line:90%
You're so busy being wholly.

00:34:10.470 --> 00:34:12.939 align:middle line:90%


00:34:12.939 --> 00:34:14.189 align:middle line:90%
Why don't you try being human.

00:34:14.189 --> 00:34:20.045 align:middle line:90%


00:34:20.045 --> 00:34:21.420 align:middle line:84%
Funny, I'd never
thought of that.

00:34:21.420 --> 00:34:22.480 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that far out?

00:34:22.480 --> 00:34:25.420 align:middle line:90%


00:34:25.420 --> 00:34:28.179 align:middle line:84%
Because somehow being human
was less than perfect.

00:34:28.179 --> 00:34:33.120 align:middle line:90%


00:34:33.120 --> 00:34:35.190 align:middle line:84%
Even though I
intellectually knew

00:34:35.190 --> 00:34:36.810 align:middle line:84%
that form is no
other than formless,

00:34:36.810 --> 00:34:38.280 align:middle line:84%
and formless is no
other than form.

00:34:38.280 --> 00:34:39.810 align:middle line:84%
And I knew that
the manifestation

00:34:39.810 --> 00:34:41.460 align:middle line:90%
was God made manifest.

00:34:41.460 --> 00:34:43.679 align:middle line:84%
Everything was perfect
out there except me.

00:34:43.679 --> 00:34:46.880 align:middle line:90%


00:34:46.880 --> 00:34:49.555 align:middle line:84%
But original sin was going to
have a last stronghold right

00:34:49.555 --> 00:34:50.355 align:middle line:90%
here.

00:34:50.355 --> 00:34:52.685 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:34:52.685 --> 00:34:53.620 align:middle line:90%


00:34:53.620 --> 00:34:56.320 align:middle line:84%
I remember being drunk with
Alan Watts in a Benedictine

00:34:56.320 --> 00:34:59.920 align:middle line:84%
monastery one night, if
you can handle that image.

00:34:59.920 --> 00:35:05.378 align:middle line:84%
And Alan said, you know,
trouble with you, Dick--

00:35:05.378 --> 00:35:07.170 align:middle line:84%
and you know you're
going to get real truth

00:35:07.170 --> 00:35:08.100 align:middle line:90%
at a moment like that.

00:35:08.100 --> 00:35:11.010 align:middle line:90%
It's like 3:00 in the morning--

00:35:11.010 --> 00:35:14.269 align:middle line:84%
he says is you're too
attached to emptiness.

00:35:14.269 --> 00:35:16.764 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:35:16.764 --> 00:35:19.259 align:middle line:90%
[APPLAUSE]

00:35:19.259 --> 00:35:26.760 align:middle line:90%


00:35:26.760 --> 00:35:30.340 align:middle line:84%
If there's one addiction
that outlasts all the others

00:35:30.340 --> 00:35:31.590 align:middle line:90%
it's the addiction to be free.

00:35:31.590 --> 00:35:34.090 align:middle line:84%
It's the addiction to come up
for air, to live in the light,

00:35:34.090 --> 00:35:36.300 align:middle line:84%
to live with love,
to be spacious,

00:35:36.300 --> 00:35:38.460 align:middle line:90%
to be present, to be ah.

00:35:38.460 --> 00:35:40.088 align:middle line:84%
Because you can see
that it can be fun,

00:35:40.088 --> 00:35:41.130 align:middle line:90%
but you're not having it.

00:35:41.130 --> 00:35:43.850 align:middle line:90%


00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:44.730 align:middle line:90%
And you feel screwed.

00:35:44.730 --> 00:35:45.980 align:middle line:90%
And why should you be screwed?

00:35:45.980 --> 00:35:47.563 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's just a
shift to your head

00:35:47.563 --> 00:35:49.510 align:middle line:90%
you got to go through.

00:35:49.510 --> 00:35:50.450 align:middle line:90%
So you get greedy.

00:35:50.450 --> 00:35:52.730 align:middle line:84%
So you start to look
for the methods.

00:35:52.730 --> 00:35:57.091 align:middle line:84%
And you try to fit them in,
take more time to do it, see?

00:35:57.091 --> 00:36:00.320 align:middle line:90%


00:36:00.320 --> 00:36:05.780 align:middle line:84%
When I went to my guru in India
and I said to him, Maharaj Ji,

00:36:05.780 --> 00:36:08.030 align:middle line:90%
how do I get free?

00:36:08.030 --> 00:36:10.840 align:middle line:90%
He said, feed people.

00:36:10.840 --> 00:36:12.565 align:middle line:90%
I said, feed people?

00:36:12.565 --> 00:36:14.440 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you don't expect--
you go all the way

00:36:14.440 --> 00:36:16.900 align:middle line:84%
to the Himalayas,
you know, and you

00:36:16.900 --> 00:36:19.210 align:middle line:84%
sit at the feet of
the guru, and you

00:36:19.210 --> 00:36:21.280 align:middle line:84%
expect him to say,
come into this cave

00:36:21.280 --> 00:36:23.960 align:middle line:84%
and I will give you
the word, you know,

00:36:23.960 --> 00:36:25.330 align:middle line:90%
and you will sit quietly.

00:36:25.330 --> 00:36:27.970 align:middle line:84%
And then you will go
through and you'll be free.

00:36:27.970 --> 00:36:29.533 align:middle line:90%
He says, feed people.

00:36:29.533 --> 00:36:30.700 align:middle line:90%
So I try a different tactic.

00:36:30.700 --> 00:36:32.760 align:middle line:84%
Maharaj Ji, how do
you get enlightened?

00:36:32.760 --> 00:36:35.380 align:middle line:90%
He says, serve people.

00:36:35.380 --> 00:36:36.520 align:middle line:90%
Well, I heard him say it.

00:36:36.520 --> 00:36:39.161 align:middle line:84%
But I figured, you
know, what does he know?

00:36:39.161 --> 00:36:41.616 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:36:41.616 --> 00:36:43.090 align:middle line:90%


00:36:43.090 --> 00:36:46.210 align:middle line:84%
He's just considering me
kind of low life, you know?

00:36:46.210 --> 00:36:48.700 align:middle line:84%
I mean, he's not
taking me seriously

00:36:48.700 --> 00:36:52.450 align:middle line:84%
as a spiritual seeker, because
the serious guys meditate.

00:36:52.450 --> 00:36:55.510 align:middle line:90%
You understand?

00:36:55.510 --> 00:37:04.650 align:middle line:84%
>> I find it humorous
to see myself trip up.

00:37:04.650 --> 00:37:09.520 align:middle line:84%
Or I see myself
wanting something.

00:37:09.520 --> 00:37:19.920 align:middle line:84%
Or like some days, my aches
and pains are so, so gorgeous

00:37:19.920 --> 00:37:23.270 align:middle line:90%
and then I complain.

00:37:23.270 --> 00:37:25.050 align:middle line:90%
Then I love it.

00:37:25.050 --> 00:37:27.960 align:middle line:90%
Me, complaining?

00:37:27.960 --> 00:37:29.300 align:middle line:90%
My god, is that you?

00:37:29.300 --> 00:37:31.870 align:middle line:90%
I mean, is that you?

00:37:31.870 --> 00:37:33.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Are you still doing that?

00:37:33.590 --> 00:37:34.390 align:middle line:90%
Still here?

00:37:34.390 --> 00:37:35.973 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, still here.

00:37:35.973 --> 00:37:38.338 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:37:38.338 --> 00:37:41.650 align:middle line:90%


00:37:41.650 --> 00:37:45.680 align:middle line:84%
>> This is where I feel there's
confusion sometimes about this

00:37:45.680 --> 00:37:46.480 align:middle line:90%
mind.

00:37:46.480 --> 00:37:49.270 align:middle line:84%
A lot of these spiritual paths,
or certainly it's all about,

00:37:49.270 --> 00:37:50.770 align:middle line:84%
we've got to control
the mind, we've

00:37:50.770 --> 00:37:52.330 align:middle line:84%
got to transcend
the mind, we've got

00:37:52.330 --> 00:37:53.950 align:middle line:84%
to unclutter the
mind, all kinds of--

00:37:53.950 --> 00:37:54.750 align:middle line:90%
>> That's true.

00:37:54.750 --> 00:37:56.420 align:middle line:90%
>> --the mind-- well, maybe.

00:37:56.420 --> 00:37:58.920 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:37:58.920 --> 00:38:02.440 align:middle line:90%


00:38:02.440 --> 00:38:04.690 align:middle line:84%
I think you'll find my
theory a little bit more

00:38:04.690 --> 00:38:06.555 align:middle line:84%
advanced, Ram Dass,
if you just listen.

00:38:06.555 --> 00:38:11.210 align:middle line:90%


00:38:11.210 --> 00:38:12.755 align:middle line:84%
I haven't got just
one mind in here.

00:38:12.755 --> 00:38:13.630 align:middle line:90%
I've got a committee.

00:38:13.630 --> 00:38:16.640 align:middle line:84%
I've got numerous people in
here immediately available.

00:38:16.640 --> 00:38:19.300 align:middle line:84%
I've got the eternal
pessimist, always

00:38:19.300 --> 00:38:21.940 align:middle line:84%
ready to paint how black
this is going to go.

00:38:21.940 --> 00:38:24.070 align:middle line:90%
I've got a raging sex maniac.

00:38:24.070 --> 00:38:28.780 align:middle line:84%
I've got a vengeful murderer
that wants to kill anybody,

00:38:28.780 --> 00:38:31.860 align:middle line:84%
I don't know, driving too
slowly in front of me.

00:38:31.860 --> 00:38:34.990 align:middle line:84%
The victim, who's constantly
looking at everything

00:38:34.990 --> 00:38:36.760 align:middle line:90%
as a persecution.

00:38:36.760 --> 00:38:40.540 align:middle line:84%
>> The mind is just
thoughts, thought--

00:38:40.540 --> 00:38:48.460 align:middle line:84%
the river of thoughts, sex
maniac-- da, da, da, da, da.

00:38:48.460 --> 00:38:50.490 align:middle line:90%
But they're still thoughts.

00:38:50.490 --> 00:38:54.250 align:middle line:84%
And we're talking
about thoughts,

00:38:54.250 --> 00:38:57.070 align:middle line:90%
not the content of thoughts.

00:38:57.070 --> 00:39:01.040 align:middle line:84%
>> You ever have an experience
where you're feeling less than

00:39:01.040 --> 00:39:01.840 align:middle line:90%
that?

00:39:01.840 --> 00:39:04.480 align:middle line:84%
And you're like, Maharaj
Ji, hello, where are--

00:39:04.480 --> 00:39:09.971 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes, yes, yes, many times.

00:39:09.971 --> 00:39:12.376 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:39:12.376 --> 00:39:15.707 align:middle line:90%


00:39:15.707 --> 00:39:17.040 align:middle line:90%
>> Look at all the great saints.

00:39:17.040 --> 00:39:19.020 align:middle line:84%
They're all as neurotic
as anybody else.

00:39:19.020 --> 00:39:21.600 align:middle line:90%


00:39:21.600 --> 00:39:25.090 align:middle line:84%
It's just that it's
kind of irrelevant.

00:39:25.090 --> 00:39:27.280 align:middle line:84%
And so you don't have
to change your neuroses.

00:39:27.280 --> 00:39:30.537 align:middle line:84%
You just stop
identifying with them.

00:39:30.537 --> 00:39:33.120 align:middle line:84%
Then you just make friends with
them and they come by for tea.

00:39:33.120 --> 00:39:38.020 align:middle line:90%


00:39:38.020 --> 00:39:42.370 align:middle line:84%
>> A lot of people respond to
that uncertainty and anxiety

00:39:42.370 --> 00:39:43.390 align:middle line:90%
with fear.

00:39:43.390 --> 00:39:46.300 align:middle line:84%
And the way they
dissipate their fear--

00:39:46.300 --> 00:39:47.830 align:middle line:90%
there's various strategies.

00:39:47.830 --> 00:39:50.320 align:middle line:84%
One strategy is to
just buy more stuff,

00:39:50.320 --> 00:39:52.840 align:middle line:84%
to get more pleasure
now, because it's all

00:39:52.840 --> 00:39:54.040 align:middle line:90%
going to be gone soon.

00:39:54.040 --> 00:39:54.840 align:middle line:90%
That's one thing.

00:39:54.840 --> 00:39:57.472 align:middle line:90%
That's the materialist strategy.

00:39:57.472 --> 00:39:58.930 align:middle line:84%
There is another
alternative, which

00:39:58.930 --> 00:40:03.250 align:middle line:84%
is to feel that you will reduce
the fear if you align yourself

00:40:03.250 --> 00:40:05.110 align:middle line:90%
with good as opposed to evil.

00:40:05.110 --> 00:40:07.750 align:middle line:84%
In other words, it's in
the world of good and evil,

00:40:07.750 --> 00:40:09.880 align:middle line:84%
and if you are
part of the elect,

00:40:09.880 --> 00:40:13.090 align:middle line:84%
or part of the good guys, and
you push away the bad guys,

00:40:13.090 --> 00:40:16.360 align:middle line:84%
somehow you will be protected
from the uncertainties

00:40:16.360 --> 00:40:17.560 align:middle line:90%
of the world.

00:40:17.560 --> 00:40:20.660 align:middle line:84%
People grab on to
a belief system,

00:40:20.660 --> 00:40:23.560 align:middle line:84%
which makes them feel that
they are in the right.

00:40:23.560 --> 00:40:26.140 align:middle line:84%
And it reduces some
of their anxiety.

00:40:26.140 --> 00:40:27.820 align:middle line:84%
In order to hold
onto that, they have

00:40:27.820 --> 00:40:30.260 align:middle line:84%
got to convince themselves
that other people are not

00:40:30.260 --> 00:40:31.060 align:middle line:90%
in the right.

00:40:31.060 --> 00:40:32.860 align:middle line:84%
They've got to
polarize the world.

00:40:32.860 --> 00:40:36.100 align:middle line:84%
And they create a lot
of, ours as the only way,

00:40:36.100 --> 00:40:39.850 align:middle line:84%
and if you don't do it, you're
missing it and you're wrong.

00:40:39.850 --> 00:40:43.150 align:middle line:84%
What you have to have is
just a lot of compassion

00:40:43.150 --> 00:40:45.683 align:middle line:84%
for the stages
other people are in.

00:40:45.683 --> 00:40:47.162 align:middle line:90%
>> Hello?

00:40:47.162 --> 00:40:50.230 align:middle line:90%
>> I've got a great idea.

00:40:50.230 --> 00:40:53.890 align:middle line:84%
>> And I would say that souls
are neither good nor evil.

00:40:53.890 --> 00:40:55.690 align:middle line:90%
That actions are good and evil.

00:40:55.690 --> 00:40:57.280 align:middle line:90%
Motivation is good and evil.

00:40:57.280 --> 00:40:59.890 align:middle line:84%
That the personalities
can be good or evil.

00:40:59.890 --> 00:41:02.580 align:middle line:84%
But that the essence of a
being is neither good nor evil,

00:41:02.580 --> 00:41:04.210 align:middle line:90%
it just is.

00:41:04.210 --> 00:41:07.990 align:middle line:84%
And it has heavy stuff to work
out and good stuff to work out.

00:41:07.990 --> 00:41:10.090 align:middle line:84%
And you begin to
look at human beings

00:41:10.090 --> 00:41:15.580 align:middle line:84%
as having very dark karma at
times, very heavy stuff they're

00:41:15.580 --> 00:41:17.980 align:middle line:84%
carrying with them
that makes them project

00:41:17.980 --> 00:41:19.690 align:middle line:84%
into the world in
a way that creates

00:41:19.690 --> 00:41:22.640 align:middle line:84%
immense suffering
for other people.

00:41:22.640 --> 00:41:24.520 align:middle line:84%
And there is a
point in your being

00:41:24.520 --> 00:41:28.090 align:middle line:84%
where you feel this
incredible compassion

00:41:28.090 --> 00:41:31.630 align:middle line:84%
for the horror of that
predicament, for that being.

00:41:31.630 --> 00:41:34.480 align:middle line:84%
The minute you identify
them with the acts that

00:41:34.480 --> 00:41:36.880 align:middle line:84%
are creating the
suffering, you lock them

00:41:36.880 --> 00:41:41.170 align:middle line:84%
in to continuing to be who
they are with your mind.

00:41:41.170 --> 00:41:44.480 align:middle line:84%
So the art is to see actions
as evil, but not beings.

00:41:44.480 --> 00:41:47.931 align:middle line:90%


00:41:47.931 --> 00:41:50.396 align:middle line:90%
[BELL RINGING]

00:41:50.396 --> 00:41:59.290 align:middle line:90%


00:41:59.290 --> 00:42:02.230 align:middle line:10%
>> You climb a mountain,
you follow a path,

00:42:02.230 --> 00:42:05.050 align:middle line:10%
you do any of the methods
that you are attracted to.

00:42:05.050 --> 00:42:12.580 align:middle line:10%
For example, quieting your
mind, or opening your heart,

00:42:12.580 --> 00:42:16.070 align:middle line:10%
like meditating or singing
or going to church or service

00:42:16.070 --> 00:42:19.480 align:middle line:10%
or whatever, or pitying the mind
against the mind through zen

00:42:19.480 --> 00:42:21.250 align:middle line:10%
koans, or whatever.

00:42:21.250 --> 00:42:23.920 align:middle line:10%
All of it will push
you and push you.

00:42:23.920 --> 00:42:28.180 align:middle line:10%
But sooner or later, you'll
get trapped by your methods,

00:42:28.180 --> 00:42:29.410 align:middle line:10%
and they'll keep you sleep.

00:42:29.410 --> 00:42:31.900 align:middle line:10%
And you'll become
a good meditator.

00:42:31.900 --> 00:42:35.020 align:middle line:10%
Or you know, I love
Christ, but it'll

00:42:35.020 --> 00:42:37.600 align:middle line:10%
be a sleep kind of statement.

00:42:37.600 --> 00:42:40.840 align:middle line:10%
And then you'll have to
let go of that one too.

00:42:40.840 --> 00:42:43.990 align:middle line:10%
But all of these are useful
techniques to keep working.

00:42:43.990 --> 00:42:47.320 align:middle line:10%
And you've got to hear
what your own technique is.

00:42:47.320 --> 00:42:48.880 align:middle line:10%
The first thing is
not to be bugged

00:42:48.880 --> 00:42:50.740 align:middle line:10%
