But if you used either
a little bigger frame

00:49:49.560 --> 00:49:51.240 align:middle line:84%
or painted a little
smaller cloud,

00:49:51.240 --> 00:49:54.120 align:middle line:84%
you'd see that there's
a little blue sky

00:49:54.120 --> 00:49:55.330 align:middle line:90%
around the edge of the cloud.

00:49:55.330 --> 00:49:57.270 align:middle line:90%
And you'd say, oh, a cloud.

00:49:57.270 --> 00:49:58.950 align:middle line:90%
What do you know?

