for everybody to see.

00:54:54.450 --> 00:54:55.450 align:middle line:90%
The body is right there.

00:54:55.450 --> 00:54:56.380 align:middle line:90%
It's not in a box.

00:54:56.380 --> 00:54:58.950 align:middle line:90%
It's not hidden.

00:54:58.950 --> 00:55:00.690 align:middle line:90%
Most people are dying at home.

00:55:00.690 --> 00:55:03.330 align:middle line:84%
So that most people,
as they grow up,

00:55:03.330 --> 00:55:06.930 align:middle line:84%
have been in the presence
of someone dying.

00:55:06.930 --> 00:55:10.920 align:middle line:84%
While in our culture, an
amazing number of people,

00:55:10.920 --> 00:55:13.230 align:middle line:84%
even at middle age, have
never been in the presence

00:55:13.230 --> 00:55:15.530 align:middle line:90%
of someone dying.

00:55:15.530 --> 00:55:18.146 align:middle line:84%
They have walked away from
it and hidden from it.

00:55:18.146 --> 00:55:24.470 align:middle line:90%


00:55:24.470 --> 00:55:28.730 align:middle line:84%
Dear friend, please
know as you pass by,

00:55:28.730 --> 00:55:35.380 align:middle line:84%
as you are now, so once was I.
As I am now, so you will be,

00:55:35.380 --> 00:55:39.780 align:middle line:90%
prepare yourself to follow me.

00:55:39.780 --> 00:55:42.311 align:middle line:90%
And we are preparing ourselves.

00:55:42.311 --> 00:55:47.130 align:middle line:90%


00:55:47.130 --> 00:55:51.690 align:middle line:84%
I'm one of the
strange people that

00:55:51.690 --> 00:55:54.810 align:middle line:84%
absolutely delights and
enjoys being with people

00:55:54.810 --> 00:55:57.320 align:middle line:90%
as they're dying.

00:55:57.320 --> 00:56:03.200 align:middle line:84%
In fact, it is such
incredible grace for me

00:56:03.200 --> 00:56:04.970 align:middle line:84%
that in the morning
when I know I'm

00:56:04.970 --> 00:56:06.740 align:middle line:84%
going to be with
such a person, I

00:56:06.740 --> 00:56:12.770 align:middle line:84%
get absolutely thrilled
in my body and my being,

00:56:12.770 --> 00:56:15.080 align:middle line:84%
because I know I'm going
to have an opportunity

00:56:15.080 --> 00:56:16.535 align:middle line:90%
to be in the presence of truth.

00:56:16.535 --> 00:56:21.240 align:middle line:90%


00:56:21.240 --> 00:56:24.550 align:middle line:10%
While I wouldn't lay
suffering on anybody,

00:56:24.550 --> 00:56:27.540 align:middle line:10%
I have sat with people that
are suffering incredibly

00:56:27.540 --> 00:56:30.840 align:middle line:10%
with various kinds of
cancer and other kinds

00:56:30.840 --> 00:56:34.420 align:middle line:10%
of physical conditions.

00:56:34.420 --> 00:56:37.180 align:middle line:10%
And I will tell you that I
have watched people with egos

00:56:37.180 --> 00:56:38.950 align:middle line:10%
that are like cinder blocks.

00:56:38.950 --> 00:56:43.360 align:middle line:84%
They're so heavy and thick
and busy with themselves

00:56:43.360 --> 00:56:47.044 align:middle line:84%
and their self-pity and their
anger and their ah, ah, ah.

00:56:47.044 --> 00:56:50.710 align:middle line:84%
And I've watched the suffering
eat away and eat away

00:56:50.710 --> 00:56:53.500 align:middle line:90%
and eat away and eat away.

00:56:53.500 --> 00:56:57.210 align:middle line:84%
And then I've watched--
it's like the shell cracks.

00:56:57.210 --> 00:57:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And it's like the
spirit is born.

00:57:00.160 --> 00:57:02.360 align:middle line:10%
And I see them often
very close to death.

00:57:02.360 --> 00:57:07.270 align:middle line:84%
And they are like great,
wise, spiritual beings.

00:57:07.270 --> 00:57:10.060 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't think there was
a chance of a snowball in hell

00:57:10.060 --> 00:57:12.490 align:middle line:84%
that person was ever going to
come up for air spiritually

00:57:12.490 --> 00:57:16.030 align:middle line:90%
in this lifetime.

00:57:16.030 --> 00:57:19.420 align:middle line:84%
Doctors are eager to
take away people's pain.

00:57:19.420 --> 00:57:20.980 align:middle line:84%
But from a spiritual
point of view,

00:57:20.980 --> 00:57:23.500 align:middle line:84%
I look and I see the way
in which pain deepens

00:57:23.500 --> 00:57:25.060 align:middle line:90%
compassion and pain awakens.

00:57:25.060 --> 00:57:26.560 align:middle line:90%
What am I to do?

00:57:26.560 --> 00:57:28.570 align:middle line:90%
Are doctor's evil?

00:57:28.570 --> 00:57:30.487 align:middle line:90%
Are they good?

00:57:30.487 --> 00:57:32.320 align:middle line:84%
Don't you think they
should ask the patient,

00:57:32.320 --> 00:57:35.450 align:middle line:84%
do you want to get
rid of your pain?

00:57:35.450 --> 00:57:38.560 align:middle line:84%
I mean, these are all
very interesting issues

00:57:38.560 --> 00:57:40.780 align:middle line:84%
about how you help without
getting caught and being

00:57:40.780 --> 00:57:43.660 align:middle line:84%
a helper, and seeing the other
person as somebody that needs

00:57:43.660 --> 00:57:45.940 align:middle line:90%
help and still helping them.

00:57:45.940 --> 00:57:48.760 align:middle line:90%


00:57:48.760 --> 00:57:51.100 align:middle line:84%
And when I said to
Emmanuel, Emmanuel,

00:57:51.100 --> 00:57:53.950 align:middle line:84%
I deal a lot with
the fear of dying

00:57:53.950 --> 00:57:56.350 align:middle line:90%
in this culture and death.

00:57:56.350 --> 00:57:59.200 align:middle line:90%
What should I tell people?

00:57:59.200 --> 00:58:04.990 align:middle line:84%
And he said, Ram Dass, tell them
that death is absolutely safe.

00:58:04.990 --> 00:58:07.892 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:58:07.892 --> 00:58:10.100 align:middle line:84%
I just put those two things
together and realize what

00:58:10.100 --> 00:58:11.870 align:middle line:90%
a far out line that is.

00:58:11.870 --> 00:58:13.700 align:middle line:90%
Death is absolutely safe.

00:58:13.700 --> 00:58:15.200 align:middle line:84%
And then he added
one more image.

00:58:15.200 --> 00:58:18.845 align:middle line:84%
He said, it's like
taking off a tight shoe.

00:58:18.845 --> 00:58:21.530 align:middle line:90%


00:58:21.530 --> 00:58:22.610 align:middle line:90%
Can you hear that one?

00:58:22.610 --> 00:58:25.580 align:middle line:90%
Like taking off a tight shoe.

00:58:25.580 --> 00:58:29.240 align:middle line:84%
Now, just imagine that you,
as spirit or awareness,

00:58:29.240 --> 00:58:32.450 align:middle line:84%
have contained yourself
in an incarnation,

00:58:32.450 --> 00:58:36.080 align:middle line:84%
or contained it in a
conceptual model of who you are

00:58:36.080 --> 00:58:38.270 align:middle line:90%
and on storyline.

00:58:38.270 --> 00:58:41.210 align:middle line:84%
And then at some point,
you dissolve out of that.

00:58:41.210 --> 00:58:44.810 align:middle line:84%
You break out of that, and there
is this incredible relationship

00:58:44.810 --> 00:58:46.786 align:middle line:90%
quality.

00:58:46.786 --> 00:58:51.030 align:middle line:84%
And I came into the room,
and Jeannie had cancer

00:58:51.030 --> 00:58:55.800 align:middle line:90%
of the cervix, very painful.

00:58:55.800 --> 00:58:57.340 align:middle line:90%
She was writhing in pain.

00:58:57.340 --> 00:59:00.150 align:middle line:84%
It was a collaborative process
with the doctor and she

00:59:00.150 --> 00:59:03.720 align:middle line:84%
and Laura, all deciding pain
medicine and how long she'd

00:59:03.720 --> 00:59:04.710 align:middle line:90%
live and things.

00:59:04.710 --> 00:59:07.110 align:middle line:84%
And I came in, and I
sat down and she usually

00:59:07.110 --> 00:59:09.180 align:middle line:84%
would fight me tooth and
nail, because she was

00:59:09.180 --> 00:59:11.190 align:middle line:90%
very much of an intellectual.

00:59:11.190 --> 00:59:12.780 align:middle line:84%
But she was so
weak this time, she

00:59:12.780 --> 00:59:14.910 align:middle line:90%
was just writhing on the bed.

00:59:14.910 --> 00:59:17.070 align:middle line:84%
So I sat down next
to the bed and I just

00:59:17.070 --> 00:59:20.490 align:middle line:84%
did this meditation,
the Buddhist meditation

00:59:20.490 --> 00:59:23.190 align:middle line:90%
that is done in cemeteries.

00:59:23.190 --> 00:59:24.810 align:middle line:84%
Usually they have
a bloated corpse,

00:59:24.810 --> 00:59:29.220 align:middle line:84%
or a fly-infested corpse, or
a skeleton to meditate upon.

00:59:29.220 --> 00:59:31.770 align:middle line:84%
In this case, I just had
this decaying body before me.

00:59:31.770 --> 00:59:35.940 align:middle line:84%
And I just sat,
allowing it to exist,

00:59:35.940 --> 00:59:39.020 align:middle line:84%
watching all my emotional
reactions to it,

00:59:39.020 --> 00:59:40.290 align:middle line:90%
just allowing it to exist.

00:59:40.290 --> 00:59:43.510 align:middle line:90%


00:59:43.510 --> 00:59:45.480 align:middle line:90%
And I became so peaceful.

00:59:45.480 --> 00:59:47.340 align:middle line:90%
And the room was so clear.

00:59:47.340 --> 00:59:49.800 align:middle line:84%
It was a purpley
light in the room.

00:59:49.800 --> 00:59:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And she turned to me,
all the time her body

00:59:51.960 --> 00:59:55.650 align:middle line:84%
is writhing in pain,
and she says to me,

00:59:55.650 --> 00:59:58.580 align:middle line:84%
I've never felt so much
ecstasy in my life.

00:59:58.580 --> 01:00:01.080 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't rather be anywhere
else than here at this moment.

01:00:01.080 --> 01:00:04.680 align:middle line:90%


01:00:04.680 --> 01:00:06.870 align:middle line:84%
And she sits up
and she is radiant.

01:00:06.870 --> 01:00:08.460 align:middle line:84%
And she comes over
and she starts

01:00:08.460 --> 01:00:14.190 align:middle line:84%
to stroke my face as if she
is looking at a human being,

01:00:14.190 --> 01:00:15.780 align:middle line:90%
at this phenomenon of a body.

01:00:15.780 --> 01:00:18.240 align:middle line:90%
And she's tenderly stroking it.

01:00:18.240 --> 01:00:21.570 align:middle line:90%
And I stroke her face.

01:00:21.570 --> 01:00:24.810 align:middle line:84%
And then she comes
up and she kisses me.

01:00:24.810 --> 01:00:27.090 align:middle line:84%
And I kiss her and
we hold each other.

01:00:27.090 --> 01:00:30.900 align:middle line:90%


01:00:30.900 --> 01:00:34.140 align:middle line:84%
And it's a moment
that is absolutely

01:00:34.140 --> 01:00:37.350 align:middle line:90%
perfect in his presence.

01:00:37.350 --> 01:00:41.380 align:middle line:84%
I mean, even the little tiny
thought forms in my head like,

01:00:41.380 --> 01:00:45.060 align:middle line:84%
well, this is the next thing
to necrophilia, you know.

01:00:45.060 --> 01:00:48.490 align:middle line:84%
Do you know her
husband is downstairs?

01:00:48.490 --> 01:00:49.350 align:middle line:90%
They're Quakers.

01:00:49.350 --> 01:00:50.558 align:middle line:90%
What will they think of this?

01:00:50.558 --> 01:00:52.920 align:middle line:84%
And you know, all those little
"niggily, piggily" things

01:00:52.920 --> 01:00:57.300 align:middle line:84%
in my head were just like
little lights around the edge.

01:00:57.300 --> 01:00:59.310 align:middle line:84%
They didn't have much
juice to them, you know,

01:00:59.310 --> 01:01:01.650 align:middle line:84%
because the whole thing
was just what it was.

01:01:01.650 --> 01:01:04.710 align:middle line:90%
It was actually perfect.

01:01:04.710 --> 01:01:06.300 align:middle line:84%
And then she laid
back on the pillow,

01:01:06.300 --> 01:01:08.268 align:middle line:84%
and we held hands
about 10 or 15 minutes.

01:01:08.268 --> 01:01:10.560 align:middle line:84%
And I said, well, Jean, you
understand everything I do.

01:01:10.560 --> 01:01:12.140 align:middle line:84%
There's no more
sense wasting time.

01:01:12.140 --> 01:01:16.130 align:middle line:84%
See you around,
namaste, namaste.

01:01:16.130 --> 01:01:16.930 align:middle line:90%
And I left.

01:01:16.930 --> 01:01:18.780 align:middle line:84%
And I flew down to
New York that night,

01:01:18.780 --> 01:01:20.530 align:middle line:84%
and the next morning
at 7:00 I got a call.

01:01:20.530 --> 01:01:21.613 align:middle line:90%
She died during the night.

01:01:21.613 --> 01:01:27.090 align:middle line:90%


01:01:27.090 --> 01:01:33.300 align:middle line:84%
The more you are aware of
the spiritual nature of life,

01:01:33.300 --> 01:01:43.060 align:middle line:84%
the more you see the moment of
death as a moment for release,

01:01:43.060 --> 01:01:46.440 align:middle line:90%
for taking off the tight shoe.

01:01:46.440 --> 01:01:53.050 align:middle line:10%
And the art form in dying is
that, at the moment of death,

01:01:53.050 --> 01:01:58.710 align:middle line:10%
you are neither grabbing at
life, nor pushing it away.

01:01:58.710 --> 01:02:00.630 align:middle line:84%
You are neither
pushing, nor pulling.

01:02:00.630 --> 01:02:07.260 align:middle line:84%
It's the attraction and aversion
that keeps you holding to form.

01:02:07.260 --> 01:02:13.200 align:middle line:84%
So to prepare for the moment of
death, when the processes that

01:02:13.200 --> 01:02:18.450 align:middle line:84%
go on in consciousness are
a dissolving of boundaries,

01:02:18.450 --> 01:02:23.640 align:middle line:84%
a speeding up of awareness,
an opening and expanding,

01:02:23.640 --> 01:02:33.410 align:middle line:84%
to be in that process where
you don't go, no and grab hold,

01:02:33.410 --> 01:02:35.300 align:middle line:90%
one prepares.

01:02:35.300 --> 01:02:37.310 align:middle line:84%
One prepares for
the moment of death.

01:02:37.310 --> 01:02:45.800 align:middle line:90%


